text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia amyctica is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to an area in the south of the Goldfields-Esperance region of Western Australia.The erect bushy pungent shrub typically grows to a height of 0.7 to 1.5 metres (2 to 5 ft). It blooms from August to September and produces yellow flowers.
